1
00:00:21,255 --> 00:00:22,455
I should die.

2
00:00:22,955 --> 00:00:27,315
A writer who can't write is dead anyway.

3
00:00:28,688 --> 00:00:30,818
Well, why do I have to die?

4
00:00:31,088 --> 00:00:33,288
Think about all the things I've been through to get here. Darn it.

5
00:00:33,588 --> 00:00:35,758
Giving something and taking it away is the worst thing one can do!

6
00:00:48,718 --> 00:00:51,388
Your life is very close with death.

7
00:00:52,188 --> 00:00:55,818
You'll meet someone every time but you can't tell good from bad.

8
00:00:59,918 --> 00:01:03,988
Soon, you will have two special encounters.

9
00:01:23,988 --> 00:01:26,958
Try hard. You can only survive that way.

10
00:01:31,918 --> 00:01:35,718
If you ever end up in the same situation, I'll just let you die.

11
00:01:35,718 --> 00:01:37,158
I won't help you!

12
00:01:57,455 --> 00:01:59,315
(Episode 3)

13
00:02:12,488 --> 00:02:13,758
What are you doing?

14
00:02:14,288 --> 00:02:17,288
Are you trying to read the flow of the energy?

15
00:02:17,488 --> 00:02:19,418
Seol's name means "snow", right?

16
00:02:19,688 --> 00:02:22,588
Yes, it does. Why are you asking out of the blue?

17
00:02:28,088 --> 00:02:29,518
What is it, Wang Bang Wool fairy?

18
00:02:30,288 --> 00:02:32,488
It's going to rain. Bring in the clean laundry.

19
00:02:33,588 --> 00:02:37,088
Doesn't the forecast say that? Stop pretending you're so psychic.

20
00:02:37,888 --> 00:02:40,958
Everyone in the industry knows that you're not that sharp anymore.

21
00:02:42,358 --> 00:02:45,488
I'm not sure whether them crossing paths is a good thing or not.

22
00:02:46,858 --> 00:02:49,718
I hope things don't get all tangled up.

23
00:02:51,888 --> 00:02:54,688
My gosh, it's really raining.

24
00:02:56,158 --> 00:03:00,458
(Sungsoocheong)

25
00:04:23,958 --> 00:04:26,558
(Carpe Diem)

26
00:04:31,478 --> 00:04:33,878
(Chicago Typewriter)

27
00:04:43,438 --> 00:04:45,878
I'm an avid fan of yours.

28
00:04:46,578 --> 00:04:50,148
Please don't worry about a thing. You'll recover soon.

29
00:04:50,648 --> 00:04:52,978
I'll take good care of you.

30
00:05:07,478 --> 00:05:08,878
Where am I?

31
00:05:09,838 --> 00:05:11,878
Who brought me here?

32
00:05:22,408 --> 00:05:24,778
("Stalker")

33
00:05:25,778 --> 00:05:27,878
This situation is...

34
00:05:35,738 --> 00:05:37,138
"Misery".

35
00:05:38,608 --> 00:05:40,138
You woke up.

36
00:05:40,408 --> 00:05:42,838
Who is she, really?

37
00:05:42,838 --> 00:05:44,178
You were very lucky.

38
00:05:44,708 --> 00:05:47,608
All the money you spent on your expensive car was worth it.

39
00:05:47,608 --> 00:05:50,408
Does she always have to hold things like a shovel and a syringe?

40
00:05:50,408 --> 00:05:52,738
Also, I happened to pass by you...

41
00:05:53,178 --> 00:05:56,508
at the perfect timing, which was lucky for you.

42
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:02,778
What do you say? Isn't it amazing enough to be called a miracle?

43
00:06:02,778 --> 00:06:06,208
For goodness' sake. What is this? Does she think I'm a dog?

44
00:06:06,208 --> 00:06:08,278
I can't really say no.

45
00:06:08,408 --> 00:06:10,908
What? Can she read my mind?

46
00:06:11,208 --> 00:06:14,378
- Is she really a psychopath? - No.

47
00:06:15,678 --> 00:06:18,508
Unfortunately, the heavy rain has seriously affected the road,

48
00:06:18,508 --> 00:06:20,308
so the rescue team can't come right away.

49
00:06:20,808 --> 00:06:25,278
I gave you first-aid treatment with things I could find in this cabin.

50
00:06:26,738 --> 00:06:28,008
All right. Now...

51
00:06:34,738 --> 00:06:36,238
Don't move.

52
00:06:36,708 --> 00:06:39,708
- If you keep moving like that... - If I keep moving... What?

53
00:06:40,038 --> 00:06:42,378
What are you going to do? Will you shoot me?

54
00:06:42,678 --> 00:06:44,338
Will you break my leg with a hammer?

55
00:06:54,508 --> 00:06:56,308
I told you to stop moving.

56
00:06:56,308 --> 00:06:58,838
I'm nervous too because I've never done this to a person before.

57
00:07:20,778 --> 00:07:23,108
What's this?

58
00:07:23,908 --> 00:07:25,408
It's liquid diet.

59
00:07:25,908 --> 00:07:28,038
I was going to spoon-feed you, but there is no spoon here.

60
00:07:28,038 --> 00:07:30,708
You should've told me first.

61
00:07:30,708 --> 00:07:32,208
After you eat, you have to take the medicine.

62
00:07:32,208 --> 00:07:36,138
No. How can I possibly know what it's for?

63
00:07:37,708 --> 00:07:40,738
You were supposed to, but I thought it would be too tough for you.

64
00:07:40,738 --> 00:07:42,408
So I ground it and put it in the liquid diet.

65
00:07:43,108 --> 00:07:44,178
Darn it.

66
00:07:44,978 --> 00:07:48,638
Why didn't you tell me first?

67
00:07:49,278 --> 00:07:52,478
You just took a strong painkiller, so you'll feel sleepy.

68
00:07:52,478 --> 00:07:54,908
Don't worry and take a nap.

69
00:07:54,908 --> 00:07:57,878
How can I not worry?

70
00:07:58,438 --> 00:08:02,878
How would I know what you're going to do while I'm asleep?

71
00:08:07,508 --> 00:08:09,378
I can't fall asleep.

72
00:08:10,008 --> 00:08:11,908
I can't fall asleep.

73
00:08:12,408 --> 00:08:14,708
I should write.

74
00:08:18,138 --> 00:08:19,778
It's 10 o'clock. Is it here?

75
00:08:19,778 --> 00:08:20,838
It's not here.

76
00:08:21,508 --> 00:08:24,538
- What do we do? - This is crazy.

77
00:08:42,378 --> 00:08:43,838
What about Mr. Han?

78
00:08:43,878 --> 00:08:46,138
He's still out of reach.

79
00:08:53,678 --> 00:08:54,908
("Chicago Typewriter" 1st week script)

80
00:08:55,778 --> 00:08:57,108
Mr. Han's script is coming.

81
00:08:57,108 --> 00:08:58,108
What?

82
00:09:03,178 --> 00:09:04,938
He worked on it with a typewriter.

83
00:09:05,208 --> 00:09:06,748
Start typing, Mi Young.

84
00:09:06,748 --> 00:09:07,908
How long does it take to type the first episode?

85
00:09:07,908 --> 00:09:09,908
I'll finish it in 10 minutes. Get me the rest as well.

86
00:09:09,908 --> 00:09:12,108
Call the website and ask for a little more time.

87
00:09:12,108 --> 00:09:14,078
- Okay. - The rest, work on social media.

88
00:09:15,138 --> 00:09:18,278
What are you doing? Get to work! Come on!

89
00:10:06,478 --> 00:10:07,808
(Wang Bang Wool Fairy)

90
00:10:07,808 --> 00:10:10,838
(Do Anything)
