91
00:10:14,838 --> 00:10:17,408
Jeon Seol.

92
00:10:35,938 --> 00:10:37,408
Dad!

93
00:10:37,508 --> 00:10:38,978
Dad!

94
00:10:38,978 --> 00:10:41,208
Are you well?

95
00:10:41,578 --> 00:10:43,838
Are you well?

96
00:10:44,438 --> 00:10:46,838
I'm well.

97
00:10:47,678 --> 00:10:50,008
I'm well.

98
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:52,578
Dad!

99
00:10:52,978 --> 00:10:55,378
- Dad! - I miss you!

100
00:10:55,378 --> 00:10:57,338
I miss you!

101
00:10:58,438 --> 00:11:02,638
Seol! Seol! My Jeon Seol!

102
00:11:03,078 --> 00:11:04,408
Come here.

103
00:11:06,678 --> 00:11:09,178
I made this swing for you.

104
00:11:11,308 --> 00:11:12,978
After living with your mom for a long time,

105
00:11:12,978 --> 00:11:15,378
is it strange to live with me for the first time?

106
00:11:16,208 --> 00:11:19,008
Right. I have a gift for you.

107
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:22,678
I found this in the snow when I went hiking.

108
00:11:22,978 --> 00:11:25,238
I think it's over 70 years old.

109
00:11:25,508 --> 00:11:26,838
It's broken,

110
00:11:27,178 --> 00:11:28,638
but doesn't it look like it would bear a great story?

111
00:11:28,678 --> 00:11:29,938
Look at it. The second hand...

112
00:11:29,938 --> 00:11:32,778
is made with gold, rather than the hour hand.

113
00:11:33,138 --> 00:11:36,338
The owner of this watch must know that...

114
00:11:36,338 --> 00:11:38,878
the small thing has to be right for the big thing to move well.

115
00:11:41,008 --> 00:11:43,708
Here. It's yours.

116
00:11:44,778 --> 00:11:47,378
From now on, don't dwell on the past.

117
00:11:47,778 --> 00:11:49,908
Don't sacrifice the present for the future.

118
00:11:50,178 --> 00:11:53,708
Be present in every minute and every second.

119
00:11:54,108 --> 00:11:55,108
Do you get me or not?

120
00:11:58,678 --> 00:12:00,078
Did I make it sound too difficult?

121
00:12:01,338 --> 00:12:02,738
What I am saying is...

122
00:12:04,508 --> 00:12:05,578
Just...

123
00:12:06,178 --> 00:12:08,808
do what you want to do...

124
00:12:08,978 --> 00:12:12,478
and enjoy every day of your life. Do you get it or not?

125
00:12:14,978 --> 00:12:15,978
I get it.

126
00:12:16,738 --> 00:12:17,878
I get it.

127
00:12:18,438 --> 00:12:21,578
I engraved your advice in my heard like a tattoo,

128
00:12:21,838 --> 00:12:24,378
and I'm always trying to enjoy my life.

129
00:12:33,778 --> 00:12:34,838
Where's my watch?

130
00:12:35,638 --> 00:12:36,708
Where did it go?

131
00:12:36,708 --> 00:12:38,008
Her father's death anniversary?

132
00:12:38,008 --> 00:12:40,578
You know that he died while rescuing a missing person, right?

133
00:12:40,638 --> 00:12:41,878
Of course.

134
00:12:41,878 --> 00:12:43,838
She scattered his ash in that mountain.

135
00:12:43,838 --> 00:12:48,408
So around this time every year, she goes there alone and spend days.

136
00:12:48,408 --> 00:12:50,338
She also goes there when she fills frustrated.

137
00:12:51,278 --> 00:12:52,808
So that's where she's gone.

138
00:12:53,308 --> 00:12:54,738
I thought it was something else.

139
00:12:54,908 --> 00:12:57,938
She's been out of touch for a month, so I thought something happened.

140
00:12:58,178 --> 00:12:59,538
What's the bad news then?

141
00:12:59,538 --> 00:13:02,078
That area is isolated because of the heavy rain.

142
00:13:03,338 --> 00:13:04,338
What?

143
00:13:37,078 --> 00:13:38,438
(Change in software license contract)

144
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:41,638
(Police)

145
00:13:42,778 --> 00:13:43,808
(No signal)

146
00:14:17,708 --> 00:14:19,138
Are you trying to escape?

147
00:14:32,338 --> 00:14:36,408
I told you that you can't escape because we are isolated.

148
00:14:36,808 --> 00:14:38,038
Don't come near me.

149
00:14:39,108 --> 00:14:40,408
Don't come near me.

150
00:14:40,508 --> 00:14:43,608
You're not well. So why do you do this?

151
00:14:44,978 --> 00:14:47,008
You should listen...

152
00:14:47,608 --> 00:14:49,678
when I talk to you nicely.

153
00:14:50,808 --> 00:14:52,038
No!

154
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:58,478
What? It's a spoon.

155
00:14:59,608 --> 00:15:01,138
You had a spoon.

156
00:15:06,308 --> 00:15:09,478
You have enough spoons to open a restaurant.

157
00:15:10,338 --> 00:15:12,278
Why did you use the syringe?

158
00:15:12,638 --> 00:15:16,078
How can I dare to feed you with that dirty spoon?

159
00:15:16,178 --> 00:15:18,638
Unspecified individuals have used them.

160
00:15:18,808 --> 00:15:21,838
Then did you tie me up because unspecified individuals...

161
00:15:21,838 --> 00:15:23,178
have used my body?

162
00:15:23,178 --> 00:15:24,678
I was worried that your bones were fractured.

163
00:15:24,678 --> 00:15:27,238
That's why I tied you up before putting on the cast.

164
00:15:27,978 --> 00:15:30,008
I released you only because you seemed to be fine.

165
00:15:31,808 --> 00:15:33,508
You're just taking revenge on me, aren't you?

166
00:15:34,038 --> 00:15:35,408
You're holding a grudge on me, aren't you?

167
00:15:35,838 --> 00:15:37,808
The former is wrong, and the latter is right.

168
00:15:37,808 --> 00:15:39,738
Goodness.

169
00:15:39,938 --> 00:15:43,238
Your grudge is as great as the Great Wall.

170
00:15:43,638 --> 00:15:47,478
I'm thankful to you for providing me good materials.

171
00:15:50,738 --> 00:15:52,538
Where are you going in the middle of the conversation?

172
00:15:53,038 --> 00:15:54,078
Where are you going?

173
00:15:54,508 --> 00:15:55,978
Can't you hear me?

174
00:15:59,678 --> 00:16:01,378
Where are you going with that shovel?

175
00:16:01,378 --> 00:16:03,038
I must have something to dig.

176
00:16:03,708 --> 00:16:06,708
Are you going to dig my grave?

177
00:16:06,708 --> 00:16:09,738
Goodness, aren't you imaginative?

178
00:16:09,978 --> 00:16:11,178
I didn't think of that.

179
00:16:13,938 --> 00:16:15,608
Will you keep being sarcastic?

180
00:16:15,908 --> 00:16:17,808
What is it that you want to know?

181
00:16:18,038 --> 00:16:19,278
Why are you here?

182
00:16:20,338 --> 00:16:22,308
Because you grabbed me.

183
00:16:25,508 --> 00:16:28,338
How did you know I was going to get into an accident here?

184
00:16:28,338 --> 00:16:31,778
How did you manage to be here just on time for it?

185
00:16:33,478 --> 00:16:35,308
Why? Do you think I planned this too?

186
00:16:35,308 --> 00:16:38,608
Are you suggesting that I did something to your car?

187
00:16:38,908 --> 00:16:42,178
Isn't it strange that there are too many coincidences?

188
00:16:42,178 --> 00:16:45,138
What do I have to do to make you stop suspecting me?

189
00:16:45,138 --> 00:16:47,478
This is my father's cabin. Are you happy now?

190
00:16:47,478 --> 00:16:49,178
I was on the way to find the keepsake from my father...

191
00:16:49,178 --> 00:16:50,478
which I lost while carrying you.

192
00:16:50,478 --> 00:16:53,008
I'm taking a shovel because I'm worried it might've been buried.

193
00:16:53,978 --> 00:16:57,408
I am the one who's curious about why you are here.

194
00:16:57,408 --> 00:16:59,478
Are you happy? Are you happy now?

195
00:17:01,708 --> 00:17:04,008
Stop screaming like a pig.

196
00:17:04,278 --> 00:17:07,778
I was crazy. I shouldn't have saved you again.

197
00:17:08,738 --> 00:17:09,738
Hey.

198
00:17:10,278 --> 00:17:12,238
What you just said...

199
00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:14,778
is very cheap.

200
00:17:14,778 --> 00:17:15,978
"He must have changed."

201
00:17:15,978 --> 00:17:18,138
"He'll learn something if I save him this time."

202
00:17:18,138 --> 00:17:20,948
"What will he say when he wakes up?"

203
00:17:20,948 --> 00:17:23,378
"If he apologizes for last time and thanks me for saving him,"

204
00:17:23,408 --> 00:17:27,078
"I'll forgive him." I was an idiot to think so.

205
00:17:28,448 --> 00:17:32,778
Don't be so harsh on yourself.

206
00:17:32,948 --> 00:17:35,508
Remember, we're isolated.

207
00:17:35,508 --> 00:17:39,508
Your body is wrecked, and you have no one but me here.

208
00:17:39,608 --> 00:17:43,008
If you want to survive, stop yelling at me and ask me for help.

209
00:17:43,778 --> 00:17:47,038
Didn't you say you'd never need anyone's help?

210
00:17:49,538 --> 00:17:51,838
What's with her attitude?

211
00:18:40,738 --> 00:18:44,578
Write. Stop acting so weak and start writing.

212
00:18:45,138 --> 00:18:47,808
It's been a month. You're not in your right mind.

213
00:18:47,808 --> 00:18:49,638
We need a solution!

214
00:18:52,838 --> 00:18:55,948
We'll lose so much if the 10 million-dollar project goes wrong.

215
00:19:47,908 --> 00:19:49,948
(Stalker)

216
00:20:07,908 --> 00:20:10,308
You said we've met before, right?

217
00:20:12,078 --> 00:20:13,408
When was it?

218
00:20:40,448 --> 00:20:41,678
Replenish your energy.

219
00:20:41,738 --> 00:20:44,238
I'm your first fan.

220
00:21:06,138 --> 00:21:08,338
Here we go.

221
00:22:26,238 --> 00:22:27,308
See?

222
00:22:27,938 --> 00:22:30,108
If you save my life,

223
00:22:31,408 --> 00:22:33,338
I save yours too.

224
00:22:36,208 --> 00:22:38,178
That's who I am.

225
00:23:03,308 --> 00:23:05,178
We're too close.

226
00:23:08,878 --> 00:23:11,908
If this turns out to be your trick, you'll be dead meat.

227
00:23:14,938 --> 00:23:16,108
Come here.

228
00:23:20,808 --> 00:23:23,438
I'm sorry for last time.

229
00:23:26,238 --> 00:23:27,538
Thank you...

230
00:23:28,338 --> 00:23:29,538
for this time.

231
00:23:32,338 --> 00:23:34,008
Gosh, it makes me cringe.

232
00:23:35,778 --> 00:23:39,038
Don't get me wrong. I'm bad at saying these things.

233
00:23:40,078 --> 00:23:43,508
That's why I try not to create situations where I have to say them.

234
00:23:43,938 --> 00:23:46,308
Why can't you trust people?

235
00:23:46,938 --> 00:23:48,938
Do you want to look like a celebrity?

236
00:23:49,208 --> 00:23:51,938
I've been stabbed in the back too many times.

237
00:23:51,938 --> 00:23:54,408
That must be why.

238
00:23:54,778 --> 00:23:56,978
Everyone gets stabbed in the back now and then.

239
00:24:00,408 --> 00:24:01,838
Let me ask you something.

240
00:24:02,038 --> 00:24:03,608
Go ahead.

241
00:24:05,538 --> 00:24:06,908
Why aren't you laughing?

242
00:24:07,808 --> 00:24:09,708
You used to laugh so much.

243
00:24:10,738 --> 00:24:13,478
It's because you said I remind you of "Misery".

244
00:24:14,138 --> 00:24:17,478
I'm not your fan anymore because you think I'm a stalker.

245
00:24:18,938 --> 00:24:20,708
Then why is your heart beating so fast?

246
00:24:23,038 --> 00:24:24,038
What are you talking about?

247
00:24:24,338 --> 00:24:25,438
Your heart.

248
00:24:26,038 --> 00:24:27,178
Don't you feel it?

249
00:24:27,208 --> 00:24:29,538
Your heart is pounding right now.

250
00:24:32,578 --> 00:24:33,738
Gosh.

251
00:25:31,308 --> 00:25:32,808
I understand.

252
00:25:34,208 --> 00:25:36,508
I understand everything.

253
00:25:37,038 --> 00:25:38,808
You can't fall asleep, right?

254
00:25:40,338 --> 00:25:44,738
This situation is what any fan would dream about.

255
00:25:45,338 --> 00:25:48,238
You don't have to try to hide your feelings.

256
00:25:50,408 --> 00:25:54,308
It'll only make you suffer.

257
00:25:56,138 --> 00:25:58,638
It's not only you.

258
00:25:59,308 --> 00:26:01,438
Don't feel too embarrassed.

259
00:26:02,808 --> 00:26:04,378
People say,

260
00:26:04,838 --> 00:26:08,638
once you fall in love with me, it's impossible to get over me.

261
00:26:11,938 --> 00:26:14,178
I now know that you're not a stalker.

262
00:26:15,508 --> 00:26:19,338
You're just a girl who is a little clumsy.

263
00:26:21,138 --> 00:26:23,208
All the misunderstandings have been cleared up.

264
00:26:25,038 --> 00:26:27,208
Now you can continue to be my fan, right?

265
00:26:42,038 --> 00:26:44,208
What is she, really?

